Get model parameters

Source: R/get_parameters.R
get_parameters.Rd

Get model parameters

Usage

get_parameters(design, model = NULL)

Arguments

design

A data.frame containing the experimental design.

model

A string specifying a model. One in supported_models().

Value

A list with model parameters depending on model

Examples

block <- get_design("blocking")
get_parameters(block, model = "SM2007")
#> $alphas
#>   L   N  US 
#> 0.4 0.4 0.4 
#> 
#> $lambdas
#>  L  N US 
#>  1  1  1 
#> 
#> $omegas
#>   L   N  US 
#> 0.2 0.2 0.2 
#> 
#> $rhos
#>  L  N US 
#>  1  1  1 
#> 
#> $gammas
#>  L  N US 
#>  1  1  1 
#> 
#> $taus
#>   L   N  US 
#> 0.2 0.2 0.2 
#> 
#> $order
#> [1] 1
#>
